          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 1848</date>.</p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">I thank you exceedingly for all<lb/> your letters
                                        having no important subject to write<lb/> upon have deferred
                                        until this moment</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have retained the Priasah[?] Books sent by
                                        you<lb/> for <persName>Carvalhos</persName> friend at
                                                  <placeName>Grenada</placeName>. I do not know him
                                        <lb/> the changes in the <placeName>English
                                                  Islands</placeName> are so great that<lb/> I doubt
                                        if the amount would be forthcoming besides the<lb/> route of
                                        the Steamer has been changed. I hold them to<lb/> your order
                                        in the mean time will endeavor to dispose of<lb/> them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">My family regret the demise of <persName>Mrs
                                                  Phillips</persName> enclosed<lb/> a letter for
                                                  <persName>Madelaine</persName> which please
                                        deliver</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">You will have read of the death of the late<lb/>
                                        <persName>King of <placeName>Denmark</placeName> Christian
                                                  the 8'</persName>. the succession of his<lb/> Son
                                                  <persName>Frederic the 7th</persName> we had a
                                        particular service on<lb/>
                                        <date>Sunday</date> Evening last for the [?] of his soul
                                        the<lb/> Synagogue was filled by all classes coulours,
                                                  <persName>Mr Nathan</persName><lb/> was happy
                                        enough to compose a Sermon or Discourse<lb/> that was highly
                                        satisfactory to all present__it has done<lb/> done us good
                                        service. We are at present quiet, the<lb/> Laws not yet
                                        returned from <placeName>Copenhagen</placeName>. I suppose
                                        that<lb/> the Kings death will be a cause of detention to
                                        them</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Have you seen <persName>Mr Carillons</persName>
                                        refutation to <persName>Mr<lb/> Pennocks</persName>
                                        affectionate address to the Jews of
                                                  <placeName>Jamaica?</placeName><lb/> it is a
                                        master piece. the Books are bought up as fast<lb/> as they
                                        can be printed, they have been sent to
                                                  <placeName>Europe</placeName><lb/> thro the
                                                  <placeName>West Indies</placeName>. his bitterest
                                        enemies, award him</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>applause merit</p>
                              <p>My Son <persName>Danie</persName> his Wife gone to the
                                                  <placeName>US</placeName><lb/> to reside he will
                                        determine <del>while</del> after his arrival which<lb/> city
                                        he will select for his abode , he is a religious worthy<lb/>
                                        young man I recommend him highly to you, he is my<lb/> son
                                        will not [?] all I feel he deserves;â€“it will<lb/> cost me
                                        great pain to put with him my consolation is<lb/> that he
                                        will succeed in <placeName>America</placeName>, his mind
                                        being firmly<lb/> bent upon living in that happy country</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I am with regards from my family</p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">Yours Sincerely</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p><persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> writes me from <placeName>New
                                                  York</placeName> that one of <persName>Dr.<lb/>
                                                  Lininthal's</persName> congregation has put him in
                                        "Hesem" is<lb/> this permitted in
                                                  <placeName>America</placeName>? to put any one in
                                        Hesem?<lb/> above all, is it permitted that a lay body should<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">dare</hi> to excommunicate its
                                        Spiritual head? I suppose<lb/> like all our benighted Rulers
                                        Wardens or Trustees as you<lb/> may call them, they have
                                        constituted themselves. Accuses<lb/> [?] Judges; I suppose
                                        if this great Body be<lb/>
                                        <sic>annalized</sic> it would be found to be composed of Old
                                        Clothes<lb/> men, Ignorant <sic>arogant</sic>_shame upon
                                        us_I trust that<lb/> the Dr. will treat them with the
                                        contempt they deserve by<lb/> depriving them of his [?]
                                        abilities the cause <persName>M Isaac</persName><lb/> writes
                                        is for transferring some of their by laws; it can be<lb/>
                                        nothing that Crime is attached to, or it would have<lb/>
                                        been blazoned about, do write the particulars.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
